<p id="Par48" class="p">Taking summations on both sides of Eq. 
 <xref rid="Equ25" ref-type="" class="xref">19c</xref> results in the global sum of marginal benefits to be equal to the weighted sum of marginal cost of abatement:
 <disp-formula id="Equ26" class="disp-formula">
  <label class="label">19d</label>
  <alternatives class="alternatives">
   <tex-math id="M73" class="tex-math">\documentclass[12pt]{minimal} \usepackage{amsmath} \usepackage{wasysym} \usepackage{amsfonts} \usepackage{amssymb} \usepackage{amsbsy} \usepackage{mathrsfs} \usepackage{upgreek} \setlength{\oddsidemargin}{-69pt} \begin{document}$$ {\sum}_{\kern0.28em i=1}^{\kern0.28em n}{P}_i\frac{u_A}{u_{y_i^c}}={\sum}_i{a}_i^L{C}_{A_i} $$\end{document}</tex-math>
   <math id="M74" display="block" class="math">
    <msubsup class="msubsup">
     <mrow class="mrow">
      <mo class="mo">∑</mo>
     </mrow>
     <mrow class="mrow">
      <mspace width="thickmathspace" class="mspace"/>
      <mi class="mi">i</mi>
      <mo class="mo">=</mo>
      <mn class="mn">1</mn>
     </mrow>
     <mrow class="mrow">
      <mspace width="thickmathspace" class="mspace"/>
      <mi class="mi">n</mi>
     </mrow>
    </msubsup>
    <msub class="msub">
     <mrow class="mrow">
      <mi class="mi">P</mi>
     </mrow>
     <mi class="mi">i</mi>
    </msub>
    <mfrac class="mfrac">
     <msub class="msub">
      <mi class="mi">u</mi>
      <mi class="mi">A</mi>
     </msub>
     <msub class="msub">
      <mi class="mi">u</mi>
      <mrow class="mrow">
       <msubsup class="msubsup">
        <mi class="mi">y</mi>
        <mi class="mi">i</mi>
        <mi class="mi">c</mi>
       </msubsup>
      </mrow>
     </msub>
    </mfrac>
    <mo class="mo">=</mo>
    <msub class="msub">
     <mrow class="mrow">
      <mo class="mo">∑</mo>
     </mrow>
     <mi class="mi">i</mi>
    </msub>
    <msubsup class="msubsup">
     <mrow class="mrow">
      <mi class="mi">a</mi>
     </mrow>
     <mi class="mi">i</mi>
     <mi class="mi">L</mi>
    </msubsup>
    <msub class="msub">
     <mrow class="mrow">
      <mi class="mi">C</mi>
     </mrow>
     <mrow class="mrow">
      <msub class="msub">
       <mi class="mi">A</mi>
       <mi class="mi">i</mi>
      </msub>
     </mrow>
    </msub>
   </math>
   <graphic xlink:href="11027_2017_9758_Article_Equ26.gif" position="anchor" class="graphic" xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink"/>
  </alternatives>
 </disp-formula>which is akin to the Samuelson condition. Note that without a permit market, marginal cost of abatement may differ between countries.
</p>
